   <head>To the Gentlemen Readers.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">T</seg>HE eye (Gentlemen) is the Iudge of beautie, the eare of vtteraunce, the sense of Art: these insuing Sonnets, (sonnes of no partiall Iudge, whose eies were acquainted with Beauties Riches, whose eares frequented to Angelicall sounds, and sense rauish<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ed with excellent Science) are now by misfortune left as Orphans: and craue desertfull acceptance of your experi<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>enst iudgements; in whom rests what euer Beautie would grace, or Art adorne. Beeing left desolate, they seeke en<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tertainment: farther they will not, how euer you accept them; better they desire not, but as you like to vse them.</p>
